SV40:
•	Dengue vector surveillance and control guideline for central, provincial, district and village level were developed and distributed to all levels;
•	Sentinel sites for larvae surveillance were set up;
•	Provided training to vector surveillance staff;
•	Started to conduct larvae surveillance and report data to central level in some selected sentinel sites
•	
Challenges
•	Limited fund to conduct larvae survey and control at some selected sentinel site;
•	Lack of equipment for Larvae survey and identification at district level;
•	Low capacity of vector surveillance staff to conduct larvae identification at district level;
•	Lack of staff and larvae survey activity are not implemented routinely due to COVID 19 situation;
•	Monitoring of larvicides/mosquito adult resistance is not implemented regularly base on research project.
